article.headline: New Hampshire 67, Harvard 60 (OT)
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Chris Vetrano banked a three-pointer with two seconds left in regulation to send the game into overtime, then Jermaine Anderson scored seven of New Hampshire's 14 OT points for Wednesday night's 67-60 victory over Harvard. Anderson, who had 17 points for the night, hit a jumper 20 seconds into overtime to give UNH the early lead, but Harvard's Kevin Rogus' three-pointer tied the game at 57. Then Anderson's next three-pointer put UNH ahead for good. Other UNH players shooting in double figures were Vetrano with 15 and Ben Sturgill with 10. Harvard's top scorer was Brian Cusworth with 18 followed by Rogus and Matt Stehle with 15 apiece. UNH stands at 4-1, Harvard at 1-3.
